# Run the Shadow Window, then Cutover

## Step

Both directions are live in shadow (first events 2026-07-16 21:23Z).
Resolved when: (1) the diff stream runs clean for a window Joel accepts
— the first finding (conversationId semantic mismatch, first diff
report) plus any successors get reconciled or explained; (2) the
remaining fit/gap canaries pass supervised: reaction on an exact
outbound message correlating to its flowId (needs the reactions bridge
or a manual probe), five-message burst preserving supersession, and a
kill/restart during ingress proving replay; (3) Joel gives the explicit
cutover go — the SDK path becomes the acting dispatcher via
`startChatSdkRuntime({legacyTransportsStopped: true})`, `notify send`
flips to the compat shim, and hand-rolled channel paths get deleted,
not abandoned. Until then the shadow just runs; the kill switch is
CHAT_SDK_INBOUND_SHADOW_ENABLED=0 + restart.

