  file SHA-256
  `567cab72113b8c2b810c6364d466b184a3a2fe63440964130fed87447e6e2321`.
- OTEL: `notify.compat_v2.confirmed` at `22:25:23.889Z` (cutover) and
  `22:45:08.145Z` (hot-dog). Handover emitted both complete five-event sequences
  at `22:24:41Z-22:24:42Z` and `22:40:51Z-22:40:52Z` with no `.failed` row.
- `/tmp/joelclaw/gateway.err:34764-34768` is a Slack shadow construction failure
  because `SLACK_BOT_TOKEN` was absent. Lines `35206-35210` are another Slack
  shadow construction failure because webhook mode lacked a signing secret or
  verifier. Neither tap error is on the Telegram outbound path. Lines
  `35920-35928` show OTEL emit timeouts for `telegram.policy.decided` and the
  old unconditional `notify.compat_v2.confirmed`; the terminal journal rows
  remain the stronger evidence.

### Fix

- Contract operator-lane messages now enter one explicit policy deliver seam at
  any urgency. The hot-dog `memory` shape reaches the Telegram adapter; only the
  explicit digest lane is digested.
- Delivery receipts now distinguish `digested` from `suppressed`. The acting shim
  derives OTEL action, level, and success from the terminal disposition instead
  of hard-coding confirmed. A confirmed receipt without a non-empty platform
  message ID is rejected as an ambiguous handled failure.
- The journal returns a durability receipt. Outbound confirmation requires both
  a non-empty adapter message ID and a durable confirmed row in ClickHouse or
  the private outbox. Flow indexing happens only after that row is durable.
- `scripts/messaging-visible-delivery-canary.ts` sends one post-flip notify event
  and exits non-zero unless a fresh Chat SDK confirmed journal row matches the
  returned Telegram chat/message composite ID. Step 3 now makes that script a
  rollback gate.
- Removed neat-memory slug `2026-07-16-59ef28c92936` from
  `~/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json` using an atomic same-directory
  replace. Readback: one entry removed, three remain, mode `0600`.

