## Telegram formatting repair — 2026-07-17

No gateway restart, acting/shadow flag change, commit, or push was performed.
The acting flag remains off and the legacy Telegram owner remains healthy.

### Source truth and fix

- `@joelclaw/markdown-formatter`'s existing `TelegramConverter` emits Telegram
  HTML. It remains unchanged because explicit HTML sends and streaming depend
  on it.
- The pinned `@chat-adapter/telegram@4.34.0` exports the MarkdownV2 converter
  the SDK itself uses. `packages/gateway/src/telegram-markdown.ts` now owns one
  shared preflight around that converter. Both paths therefore agree on
  MarkdownV2 escaping without feeding HTML into the SDK.
- Default/markdown legacy sends now use `parse_mode: "MarkdownV2"`. Conversion
  failures and unsafe overlength legacy messages become raw plain text. A
  definitive Telegram 400 gets one plain retry; ambiguous transport failures
  remain unknown and are never retried.
- Contract-v2 sends now honor the route's `formatting` field. Telegram markdown
  is preflighted and posted as SDK markdown; formatter failure becomes raw
  plain text. Plain routes post raw content. The SDK retains its own rich-message
  → MarkdownV2 → plain fallback and its 4,096-character bound.
- Blank lines remain `\n\n` paragraph boundaries. Source `- item` lines are
  normalized to visible `• item` bullets before both rendering paths, including
  plain fallback.

### Verification

- Focused legacy/helper/SDK suite — 27 pass, 0 fail. Fixtures cover two
  paragraphs, a three-item bullet list, bold, link, emoji, and MarkdownV2-hostile
  `. ! - ( )` characters.
- The same suite proves legacy and SDK MarkdownV2 400 fallback, no retry after
  ambiguous legacy transport failure or SDK 5xx, and bounded SDK formatted/plain
  payloads.
- `bun test packages/gateway/src` — 184 pass, 0 fail after the paragraph/list
  amendment and explicit plain-route bullet coverage.
- `pnpm --filter @joelclaw/markdown-formatter exec vitest run __tests__` — 21
  pass, 0 fail.
- `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit -p packages/gateway/tsconfig.json` — green.
- `bunx tsc --noEmit` — green after the paragraph/list amendment.
- Targeted Biome over all touched gateway TypeScript — green.
- `pi-notes brain check` — 235 pages, green.
- `git diff --check` — green.
- Final fresh-context review — clean; no blocker, high, or medium findings.

